      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Maximum Security Adolescent</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dr Frederick Garbrecht letter on Margaret Talbot's September 10 article opposes keeping adolescent criminals in adult prisons (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Children and adolescents possess neither a constituency nor political power, and it shows. Far too many live in poverty and many more receive inadequate and substandard educations. Now this vulnerable population has been forsaken by the criminal justice system, in a bow to political expediency, to appear tough on crime. It is a crime (or should be) to throw away the opportunity to reclaim these young people by locking them up in adult prisons and throwing away the key.</p>
        <p>Frederick Garbrecht, M.D.  Philadelphia</p>
      </block>
